gomodel:SYNGO_4077  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1: Bath application of ANP decreased the frequency of isolated glycinergic sIPSCs significantly (1Ba and 1Ca) without affecting their amplitude distribution (1Bb and 1Cb).\n\nFigure 4: Bath application of anantin, a NPR-A specific antagonist inhibits the effect of ANP on both sIPSCs and eIPSCs.\n\n11/01/2021 Dnyanada: The paper shows that the neuropeptide ANP plays a role in presynaptic modulation of glycinergic transmission in spinal neurons.. Experimental description: Wistar rats (11-19 days old) were used in this study." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-18" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4077" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

